{"copyright": {"licenseType": "NO", "determinationType": "OTHER", "thirdPartyContentCondition": "NOT_SET"}, "subjectCategories": ["INSTRUMENTATION AND PHOTOGRAPHY"], "exportControl": {"isExportControl": "NO", "ear": "NO", "itar": "NO"}, "created": "2013-08-09T10:25:00.0000000+00:00", "distributionDate": "2011-08-16T00:00:00.0000000+00:00", "center": {"code": "CDMS", "name": "Legacy CDMS", "id": "092d6e0881874968859b972d39a888dc"}, "onlyAbstract": false, "sensitiveInformation": 2, "abstract": "An experimental device successfully upconverts IR radiation in the 3.2-5.0 micron wavelength range simultaneously to visible light at 0.80-0.88 microns, while preserving frequency coding and is thus applicable to IR spectroscopy. The 1.8-micron bandwidth of IR radiation that is upconverted without temperature or phase match tuning is the largest yet reported. The over-all system quantum efficiency of the upconverter/spectrometer system is 0.01% and could be improved to 0.4%.", "title": "Upconversion of broadband infrared spectra", "stiType": "REPRINT", "distribution": "PUBLIC", "submittedDate": "2013-08-09T10:25:00.0000000+00:00", "isLessonsLearned": false, "authorAffiliations": [{"sequence": 0, "submissionId": 19780048721, "meta": {"author": {"name": "Gurski, T. R."}, "organization": {"name": "MIT, Lincoln Laboratory, Lexington", "location": "Mass., United States"}}, "id": "3533b0133ad34ee394ebdb7d5fea5f93"}, {"sequence": 1, "submissionId": 19780048721, "meta": {"author": {"name": "Epps, H. W."}, "organization": {"name": "California, University", "location": "Los Angeles, Calif., United States"}}, "id": "dae9101ec3bb4130984c2418057128b3"}, {"sequence": 2, "submissionId": 19780048721, "meta": {"author": {"name": "Maran, S. P."}, "organization": {"name": "NASA Goddard Space Flight Center", "location": "Laboratory for Astronomy and Solar Physics, Greenbelt, Md., United States"}}, "id": "9bbc4b8604214163b735f0062b6d4bf8"}], "disseminated": "METADATA_ONLY", "stiTypeDetails": "Repri